The paper deals with planning problems, which are a core topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It specifically focuses on planning with unary operators, which is a subfield of planning (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the causal graph structure of the domains, which is a topic in logic and reasoning (cs.LO). The study of the complexity of planning problems is related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC), and the use of graphs is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
